.TH CLAUDE-MONITOR 1 "2026-05-26" "claude-monitor 0.1.6" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
claude-monitor \- Linux usage widget and CLI for Claude AI subscriptions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B claude-monitor
[\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B claude-monitor
tracks Claude AI subscription usage (session 5-hour and weekly 7-day quotas)
and displays the current utilization in your system tray. A CLI surface lets
you query the same data for waybar, polybar, tmux, shell prompts, and scripts.

The app is a companion to Claude Code. On every poll it reads the live OAuth
access token from \fI~/.claude/.credentials.json\fR and calls Anthropic's
\fI/api/oauth/usage\fR endpoint. It does not store credentials, manage logins,
or support multiple accounts \(em those are Claude Code's responsibility. To
switch the active account, run \fIclaude /login\fR.

Bare invocation launches the tray. Use subcommands for non-GUI access.

.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\fBtray\fR [\fB--detach\fR]
Launch the system tray (default if no subcommand given). \fB--detach\fR forks
a new session and returns immediately so the parent shell isn't blocked.
.TP
\fBstatus\fR [\fB--json\fR | \fB--format\fR \fITPL\fR | \fB--quiet\fR]
Print the latest usage reading.
.TP
\fBpoll\fR
Force a poll cycle. Delegates to the running tray via D-Bus when possible,
falling back to an in-process poll otherwise.
.TP
\fBversion\fR
Print the binary version and exit.
.TP
\fBhelp\fR
Print top-level help.

.SH STATUS OUTPUT FORMATS
.TP
plain (default)
Human-readable single line.
.TP
\fB--json\fR
Machine-readable JSON object suitable for jq.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fITEMPLATE\fR
Go text/template against the same fields as \fB--json\fR. Useful for
status-bar integrations.
Example: \fIclaude-monitor status --format='LLM {{.PrimaryPercent}}%%'\fR

.SH EXIT CODES (\fBstatus\fR)
.TP
0
Primary usage below 75%.
.TP
10
At or above 75% (caution).
.TP
20
At or above 90% (warning).
.TP
30
At or above 95% (critical).
.TP
1
Error: no data, network failure, no Claude Code credentials file, etc.

.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.claude/.credentials.json\fR
Claude Code's OAuth credentials file. Read on every poll. Not modified by
claude-monitor.
.TP
\fI~/.local/share/claude-monitor/usage.db\fR
SQLite database (WAL). Holds only the usage history timeline. Permissions
enforced at 0600 / 0700.
.TP
\fI~/.config/claude-monitor/config.toml\fR
TOML configuration. Auto-created on first run.
.TP
\fI~/.local/state/claude-monitor/debug.log\fR
Rolling slog JSON log.
.TP
\fI~/.config/autostart/claude-monitor.desktop\fR
Autostart entry; presence controlled by the Settings window.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Launch the tray detached
\fIclaude-monitor tray --detach\fR
.TP
Waybar custom module
\fI{"custom/claude": {"exec": "claude-monitor status --format='{{.PrimaryPercent}}%%'", "interval": 60}}\fR
.TP
tmux right-status
\fIset -g status-right '#(claude-monitor status --format=\(dq{{.PrimaryPercent}}%%\(dq)'\fR
.TP
Shell warning above 75%
\fIif ! claude-monitor status --quiet; then echo "Claude usage high!"; fi\fR

